<paragraph blockId="19.[136,1452,662,1049]" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,698,724]" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">Notes:—</emphasis>
The illustration of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Lindl." box="[512,623,698,724]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Humboltia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[512,623,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">M. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Luer, C. A." box="[665,803,698,725]" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" pagination="1 - 128" refId="ref29681" refString="Luer, C. A. (1992) Icones pleurothallidinarum IX. Systematic of Myoxanthus. Addenda to Platystele, Pleurothallis, subgenus Scopula and Scaphosepalum (Orchidaceae). Monographs in Systematic Botany, Missouri Botanical Garden 44: 1 - 128." type="journal article" year="1992">Luer (1992)</bibRefCitation>
based on a plant collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1157,1250,698,724]" name="Ecuador" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
is similar to that presented here in Fig. 12A, also from 
<collectingCountry box="[575,671,734,760]" name="Ecuador" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. However, the 
<typeStatus box="[843,891,735,761]" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Lindl." box="[932,1041,734,760]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Humboltia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[932,1041,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">M. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1243,1298,735,761]" name="Peru" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">Peru</collectingCountry>
. As indicated by Luer and demonstrated by several of his sketches at SEL, this species is highly variable. The material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Lindl." box="[1344,1451,770,796]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Humboltia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[1344,1451,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">M. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recently described and illustrated from 
<collectingCountry box="[579,701,806,832]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rojas-Alvarado, G. &amp; Karremans, A. P." box="[716,1121,806,833]" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" pagination="203 - 214" refId="ref31389" refString="Rojas-Alvarado, G. &amp; Karremans, A. P. (2017) Additions to the Costa Rican Myoxanthus (Orchidaceae: Pleurothallidinae). Lankesteriana 17: 203 - 214. https: // doi. org / 10.15517 / lank. v 17 i 2.29933" type="journal article" year="2017">Rojas-Alvarado &amp; Karremans 2017</bibRefCitation>
) is clearly similar to some of Luer’s drawing of this species, but also similar to some of Luer’s drawings of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer &amp; Hirtz" authorityYear="1992" box="[991,1113,842,868]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dasyllis">
<emphasis box="[991,1113,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">M. dasyllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(all at SEL). Some differences between the diverse material are evident, with specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[834,955,878,904]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
being morphologically more consistent with the 
<typeStatus box="[176,224,915,941]" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lehmann &amp; Kraenzlin" authorityYear="1899" box="[371,516,914,940]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="furfuracea">
<emphasis box="[371,516,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">P. furfuracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than with that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Lindl." box="[680,786,914,940]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Humboltia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[680,786,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">M. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is possible that more than one species is currently treated under the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Lindl." box="[312,419,950,976]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Humboltia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[312,419,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">M. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but with the available information it is impossible to separate these entities. Specimens from the 
<typeStatus box="[177,225,987,1013]" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Lindl." box="[355,462,986,1012]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Humboltia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[355,462,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">M. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[498,549,987,1013]" name="Peru" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">Peru</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer &amp; Hirtz" authorityYear="1992" box="[605,728,986,1012]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dasyllis">
<emphasis box="[605,728,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">M. dasyllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[764,857,986,1012]" name="Ecuador" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
need to be examined carefully, and a thorough study of the variation of this species across its distribution is needed.
